  <h3>Swing JConsole</h3>
  To use the Swing enabled JConsole with the Java plug-in (or other swing
  capable browser) choose this link:
  <p>
  
  <a href="/remote/jconsole.html">http://yourserver:port/remote/jconsole.html</a>
  <p>
  
  <h3>AWT Console</h3>
  To use the minimal (not very good) AWT based console that should work in any
  browser choose this link:
  <p>
  
  <a href="/remote/awtconsole.html">
  http://yourserver:port/remote/awtconsole.html</a>
  <p>
  
  <h3>Telnet</h3>
  
  If niether console works you may use telnet to connect to the remote bsh
  server.  The bsh telnet session server (which is used by the console applet)
  runs on the port number you specified +1 (add one to the port number of the
  http bsh server you specified).  
  <em>Note that this shell is not as friendly and you will have to type ";"
  at the end of every line</em>
  <p>
  
